As for:

“We’re all slaves to our systems…”

I would soften that slightly.

We’re certainly shaped by systems:

* habits,
* institutions,
* languages,
* cultures,
* incentives,
* biological constraints,
* personal histories.

But people also have some capacity to notice those systems and modify their relationship to them.

That’s one reason self-reflection matters.

You can’t step completely outside every system, but you can often become aware of the one you’re currently inhabiting.

And awareness creates options.

